HEADWORD: Traducible
<hw>Tra*du"ci*ble</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Capable of being
derived or propagated.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Sir M.
Hale.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Capable of being traduced or calumniated.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Traducingly</ent>⟦br⟧
